===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}

{{liushu|i}}: a mouth ({{zh-l|*口}}) with word or breath ({{zh-l|*一}}) coming out. Compare {{zh-l|*言}}, in which a small stroke on top of a bifurcated tongue ([[舌]]) is also used to represent words; see also [[四]] and [[只]]. Unrelated to [[甘]].

===Etymology===
Cognate with {{och-l|話}} according to {{zh-ref|Sagart (1999)}}; if so, it is from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*grwas||to speak; word}}, whence {{cog|bo|'''གྲོས'''་སྡུར་བྱེད་པ||to consult; to discuss}} (STEDT).

